On Jun 24, 2006, at 1:18 PM, Todd Super Bassist wrote:

>     I have a 1973 Type-2. I recently got a new exhuast system from  
> the Bus
> Depot. It has provisions on the side for an EGR tube. I was  
> considering
> whether or not it would be worth it to me to try to hook this up  
> somehow, or
> if I should just put a plate over it.

I cover them up at the exhaust and then take whatever steps are  
necessary to seal the intake where the EGR connects.

> I don't even know where this would
> connect... is it something that actually benefits in the cooling of  
> the
> engine?

I personally think they are no good for the engine. I don't like the  
lag the introduce just off idle when the EGR valve opens. I also  
think they make the engine run hot and the excess soot is a known oil  
pollutant among other things.

